body: The module named string is part of the standard Rhino.Python library. If you get this error it could be an indication that the Python module search paths are not set up correctly. It [happened to me the other day](http://python.rhino3d.com/showthread.php?t=1278) when upgrading from the Rhino 5 beta to the full commercial version. You can check your paths in the normal Python script editor (editPythonScript) under options. Hope it helps.
